346
00:20:40,180 --> 00:20:44,260
Hopefully, we can get to
reach our dream together.

347
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:05,920
[Alexander] <i>I would always say
Anthoine was one of the good guys.</i>

348
00:21:06,780 --> 00:21:09,720
I saw the crash live.

349
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:12,740
<i>It does really affect you</i>

350
00:21:12,780 --> 00:21:15,380
<i>because he was someone
who I've raced against my whole life.</i>

351
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:20,480
[Christian] <i>There's this realization
for all the drivers that,</i>

352
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:23,140
"That could've been me."

353
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:25,880
<i>You know, that is a comrade.</i>

354
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:29,580
It's someone's boyfriend,
it's someone son,

355
00:21:29,620 --> 00:21:33,800
and, uh... they're not gonna be around.

356
00:21:36,820 --> 00:21:38,340
[Pierre] <i>When you lose your best mate,</i>

357
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:41,680
you can't really describe
what goes through your mind

358
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:43,340
or even through your body, you know.

359
00:21:43,380 --> 00:21:46,520
You just feel shit
and just can't believe this.

360
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:52,220
<i>When the crash happened,
